'''[[Rolling paper]]s''' (aka Blanks) are small sheets, rolls, or leaves of [[paper]] which are sold for [[Roll-your-own|rolling]] [[cigarette]]s either by hand or with a [[rolling machine]]. When rolling a cigarette, one fills the rolling paper with [[tobacco]], [[Cannabis (drug)|cannabis]], [[cloves]], [[damiana]], [[hashish|hash]] or other [[herb]]s. The paper for holding the tobacco blend may vary in porosity to allow ventilation of the burning ember or contain materials that control the burning rate of the cigarette and stability of the produced ash. Civil War re-enactors often use cigarette rolling papers to make combustible cartridges for cap & ball rifles and revolvers.
